fields.descriptive_line: Kitchen accessories including curtains, plates, towels and brushes for a dolls' house in the style of the 1940s made in England by Roma Hopkinson in the late 1980s to late 1990s
fields.physical_description:
[room setting] Kitchen room setting with a tile effect floor. The room contains a metal tap, wooden shelves, trays, plates, curtains, apron, towels, broom, rug beater, plates, light fitting, straw hat, and dog lead. On the left hand side are two pantry cupboards containing pots, jars, and tins of pretend food.
[stoves] Metal stove painted black with red foil inside creating flame effect.
[ovens] Gas oven painted blue, cream, and black. There is a plate rack above the cooker top, a grill, and an oven at the bottom with two wire shelves. Attached to the oven is a saucepan, grill pan, and iron stand.
[sinks] Sink and draining unit with a wooden shelf beneath, concealed by a curtain. Attached to the sink is a plug and chain, teatowel, and saucepan. On the shelf are boxes and bottles of household cleaning products.
[cupboards] Wooden kitchen dresser with four drawers and a cupboard below a worktop, and two cupboards above.
[tables (support furniture)] Kitchen table painted pale green with a red, white and blue printed cloth. The table is laid with plates, bowls, cutlery, cups and saucers, and an assortment of food.
[kitchen chairs] Wooden kitchen chair with turned legs.
[step chairs] Two persian style carpets with a red, blue and green pattern.
[laundry press] Folding wooden stepladder with three steps.
[tables (support furniture)] Mangle or laundry press with two clamps which allow it to be fixed to a table or work top. The frame and handle are made from metal and the rollers are plastic.
[deck chairs] Wooden table with a pine top and dark stained legs. The table has a single drawer at one end which contains cutlery and carving equipment. On top of the table is a variety of baking utensils and equipment including a rolling pin, flour shaker, baking tray, pastry cutter, mug, milk bottle, lemons and juicer, butter, and eggs.
[pumps (machinery)] Folding deck chair made from wood with a blue and white stripy seat.
[doll's house equipment] Brass effect metal pump with black plastic hose.
[dolls' house accessories] Assortment of kitchen equipment including a painted hen in a box, fire bucket, three pails, tool box with eleven tools, china tea set, jug, paper plates, jelly mould, kettle, iron, grinder, scales, baking trays, pots and pans, brown glass wine bottles and wine rack, mixing bowls and chopping boards. Also includes a cookery book, cleaning products, and a bread bin.
[carpets] Assortment of pretend food including lemons, rashers of bacon, butter, jam tarts, bread, jelly, cake. Also includes a wicker basket with fruit, four metal food tins painted yellow and a wooden seed tray with packet of seeds.

fields.public_access_description: This house is a replica of a real house in Surrey where Roma Hopkinson lived with her family during the Second World War. Roma built this house in the 1980's, paying incredible attention to detail, reproducing ration books, identity cards, newspapers, and photo albums by reducing copies of the original versions. The photographs show her family as they appeared at that time. Each doll is also modelled on a family member with Roma appearing as one on of the children in a school dress. The house accurately reflects the wartime era, showing popular products, foodstuffs, games, and furnishings from the time.
